==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presswork
<hw>Press"work`</hw> <pr>(pr⟦ecr⟧s"w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of printing from the surface of type, plates,
or engravings in relief, by means of a press; the work so done.</def>
<rj><au>MacKellar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Work done on or by a press.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Metal Work)</fld> <def>Act or process of pressing
or drawing with dies or presses; also, the product of such
work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Cabinetmaking)</fld> <def>Work consisting of a
series of cross-grained veneers united by glue, heat, and
pressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Pottery produced by pressing clay into
molds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presswork</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Press work</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Presswork
<hw>Press"work`</hw> <pr>(pr⟦ecr⟧s"w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The work of a press agent.</def> <altsp>[Usually <asp>Press
work</asp>]</altsp> <mark>[Chiefly Theat. Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

